SIMPLE: gimp
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gimp
<hw>Gimp</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[W. <ets>gwymp</ets>
fair, neat, comely.]</ety> <def>Smart; spruce; trim; nice.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gimp</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gimp
<hw>Gimp</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>guimpe</ets>,
<ets>guimple</ets>, a nun's wimple, F. <ets>guimpe</ets>, OHG.
<ets>wimpal</ets> a veil G. <ets>wimpel</ets> pennon, pendant. See
<er>Wimple</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>A narrow ornamental fabric of
silk, woolen, or cotton, often with a metallic wire, or sometimes a
coarse cord, running through it; -- used as trimming for dresses,
furniture, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gimp nail, an upholsterer's small nail.</q>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gimp</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Gimp
<hw>Gimp</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To notch; to indent; to
jag.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gin</ent>⟦br⟧
